- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as question generation and text generation. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a reinforcement learning-based approach for the task. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with developing an AI model for natural language generation. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses a graph neural network for encoding the input passage. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with generating questions given a passage, which is a task related to information retrieval.
